sentence: Crude oil futures down 1 % after U.S. supply data .

Investing.com - Crude oil futures extended losses during U.S. morning trade on Wednesday , falling to the lowest level of the session after a U.S. government report showed oil supplies rose more-than-expected last week .
On the New York Mercantile Exchange , light sweet crude futures for delivery in May traded at USD96 .15 a barrel during U.S. morning trade , down 1.1 % on the day .
New York-traded oil prices fell by as much as 1.15 % earlier in the session to hit a daily low of USD96 .10 a barrel .
Prices traded at USD96 .47 a barrel prior to the release of the supply data .

The U.S. Energy Information Administration said in its weekly report that U.S. crude oil inventories rose by 2.7 million barrels in the week ended March 29 , above expectations for an increase of 2.2 million barrels .
Total U.S. crude oil inventories stood at 388.6 million barrels as of last week , well above the upper limit of the average range for this time of year .
The report also showed that total motor gasoline inventories decreased by 0.6 million barrels , compared to expectations for a decline of 0.9 million barrels .
Oil prices were lower earlier in the day amid concerns over the fragile U.S. economic recovery .
Payroll processing firm ADP said in a report earlier that non-farm private employment rose by a seasonally adjusted 158,000 in March , below expectations for an increase of 200,000 .
Meanwhile , the U.S. Institute of Supply Management said its non-manufacturing purchasing manager 's index fell to a five-month low of 54.4 in March from a reading of 56.0 in February .
Market players now looked ahead to Friday 's highly-anticipated U.S. monthly nonfarm payrolls report to further asses the strength of the country 's economy .
The U.S. is the world 's biggest oil consuming country , responsible for almost 22 % of global oil demand .

Elsewhere , on the ICE Futures Exchange , Brent oil futures for May delivery dropped 1.4 % to trade at USD109 .14 a barrel , with the spread between the Brent and crude contracts standing at USD12 .99 a barrel .

The spread between the two contracts continued to trade near an eight-month low , due to an improving production outlook in the North Sea and amid growing concerns over the euro zone 's economic outlook .
At the same time , U.S. oil stockpiles at Cushing , Oklahoma , the delivery point for Nymex oil futures , are declining as new pipelines relieve a supply glut there .
